- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel and efficient clustering algorithm for learning Gaussian mixture models, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed algorithm and provides bounds on the expected number of projections, which are relevant topics in data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper mentions the use of random 1-dimensional projections, which is a technique commonly used in information theory for dimensionality reduction. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the running time and sample complexity of the proposed algorithm, which are topics relevant to numerical analysis. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper mentions the generalization of the proposed algorithm to mixture distributions beyond the Gaussian model, which is a topic relevant to systems and control.
